# Composer beat — the OODA cadence hook.
#
# Fired by the kernel beat scheduler on this context's coarse cadence
# (default: every 8 phrases of 16 beats @ 120 BPM). `kj drive` publishes a
# turn request for the current context; the server's turn driver runs the
# model turn. Its ABC output is committed to the shared score on the beat,
# and MIDI is derived from that committed notation for playback — notation
# is the score, MIDI a render. This script is the user-editable seam — change
# the prompt, gate the drive on conditions, or add pre-beat bookkeeping here.
#
# No positional context: the tick lifecycle runs with this context as the
# current one, so `kj drive` targets it (avoids passing the raw id as an arg).
kj drive --prompt "Beat boundary: review your own turns so far and compose the next section as ABC notation."
